.TH XWHICH 1 "2026-05-15" "User Commands" "CLI-Improved Manual"
.SH NAME
xwhich \- locate a command and identify its type
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B xwhich
[\fINAME\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
A high-visibility replacement for the standard \fBwhich\fR utility.
.PP
Standard \fBwhich\fR often fails to report shell aliases and functions, 
creating a "blind spot" for the user. This refined version utilizes the 
shell's internal \fBtype \-a\fR mechanism to provide a complete audit 
of how a command name is resolved.
.SH ADVANTAGES
.IP \(bu 3
\fBVisibility:\fR Identifies if a command is an alias, a function, or a 
binary on the disk.
.IP \(bu 3
\fBCompleteness:\fR Lists all occurrences of the name in the user's 
\fB$PATH\fR, not just the first one.
.IP \(bu 3
\fBOrderly:\fR Displays results in the order of precedence used by the 
current shell.
.SH INSTALLATION
Copy the script from the GitHub repository to your $PATH, typically /usr/local/bin.
.SH AUTHOR
William Orian Wear (Bill Wear)
